added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds a talent competition to find a superhero worthy of joining the team.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and Robin tries everything to win.

added.title: Thanksgetting
added.description: It's Thanksgiving but the Titans are sick of the normal traditions so they create their own.

added.title: Bro-Pocalypse
added.description: When the male Titans are injured, Raven and Starfire must become bros to stop the Bropocalypse.

added.title: Spice Game
added.description: Tired of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans try their hand at spicing up their food.

added.title: Black Friday
added.description: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.

added.title: Coconut Cream Pie
added.description: The Titans are shipwrecked on a desert island and must use the island's resources to survive.

added.title: Pure Protein
added.description: Still shipwrecked on a desert island, the Titans first hold a team competition but then must avoid an alien hunter.

added.title: Oregon Trail
added.description: The Titans get into the pioneer spirit as they head west on the Oregon Trail.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Legendary Sandwich
added.description: The team goes on a series of epic quests in order to create the world's perfect sandwich.

added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Re-Run
added.description: When we last saw Gumball, he was hitting rewind on Rob's Universal Remote just in time to save himself from being trapped in The Void. The remote has now taken Gumball back to the beginning of that disastrous day. Armed with the knowledge of what this day has in store, he must try and stop Rob from destroying his life.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Ollie
added.description: When Darwin asks Gumball to teach him how to skate, Gumball makes sure he covers every aspect of the skating lifestyle from wearing the right gear, using the right terms and choosing the right board. But when Darwin finally gets his wheels rolling, he realizes there might be one important aspect of skating Gumball hasn't taught him.

added.title: The Advice
added.description: Mr. Small feels that he hasn't inspired the children of Elmore Junior High, so Gumball and Darwin try to lift his spirits.

added.title: The Signal
added.description: Gumball develops a strange stutter, and it makes him accidentally offend Darwin.

added.title: The Blame
added.description: Gumball gives Billy his first taste of videogames but the sheer excitement causes him to pass out. His mother Felicity summons the PTA and threatens to ban video games all across Elmore. Gumball and Darwin are given three chances to prove that videogames can be a force for good. But when they fail, they decide to prove books can be just as dangerous.

added.title: The Man
added.description: It's Granny Jojo's Birthday and she's brought an unexpected guest to dinner. Granny Jojo has brought a boyfriend to her birthday meal and Dad isn't happy about it. He bans Granny JoJo from ever seeing Louis again. When the kids get caught sneaking Granny Jojo out of the house, Dad challenges Louis to a man-off to prove once and for all who is the man of the house?!!

added.title: The Butterfly
added.description: Gumball learns the true meaning of the butterfly effect. In Biology class, Gumball and Darwin are waiting for a butterfly to emerge from its chrysalis. Miss Simian warns them about the Butterfly Effect whereby the flap of an insect's wings can start a tornado on the other side of the world. Paying no heed, Gumball releases the emergent butterfly into the wild, where it causes havoc upon Elmore.

added.title: The Spoiler
added.description: Can Gumball and Darwin get through a whole week without somebody ruining the movie they're planning to see? Gumball and Darwin have spent all their pocket money, so will have to wait until the following weekend to see "The Screamening." It"s the scariest film of the year. The only problem is everyone else has seen it, and won't stop talking about it. Gumball is determined to avoid all spoilers. Will he succeed?

added.title: The Fridge
added.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

added.title: The Banana
added.description: Darwin lends his pen to Banana Joe but, when it comes back chewed, Gumball's thoughts turn to revenge.

added.title: The Bumpkin
added.description: Envious of his rustic lifestyle, Gumball invites Idaho over to teach the Wattersons how to live like a potato.

added.title: The Dream
added.description: When Gumball blames Darwin for kissing Penny in his dream it threatens to tear apart their friendship, the only place you can fix a dream problem is in the dream world.

added.title: The DVD
added.description: Gumball is desperate to avoid a late fee on the rented dvd he accidentally destroyed.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: Presenting Joe Cuppa
added.description: KO tries to help his favorite comedian, Joe Cuppa.

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: We're Captured
added.description: Boxman captures KO, Enid and Rad, but seems a little distracted.

added.title: Everybody Likes Rad?
added.description: When Rad posts a video that goes viral, he tries to milk his 15 minutes of fame.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.title: Adventures in Light Distortion
added.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

added.title: Are You My Dad?
added.description: People are disappearing from Beach City, and Steven tries to solve the mystery.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: Same Old World
added.description: Steven flies around the world.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: Together Breakfast
added.description: Steven tries to get the Gems to take part in his special breakfast tradition, but instead finds himself tumbling through the magical catacombs of the Crystal Gem's temple.

added.title: So Many Birthdays
added.description: So Many Birthdays: Steven learns that the Crystal Gems are thousands of years old and decides to make up for all the thousands of birthdays they've missed.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Suspended
added.description: Clarence and Sumo hit the jackpot when they get suspended for a week, learning all sorts of different facts they'd never learn in class, but after a few days the suspension takes its toll, boredom sets in and the boys want to go back.

added.title: Hoofin' It
added.description: It's time for the annual Aberdale Greased Pig Chase and everyone's excited except Clarence. He feels so bad for poor little pig Butterscotch that he takes her place in the pig chase, running from townsfolk eager to take home the prized barrel full of hot dogs!

added.title: Chalmers Santiago
added.description: While Clarence spends a lazy Saturday playing 8-bit adventure game Dragon's Cusp, Mary asks him to return some mail to the guy across the street Chalmers Santiago, whom they've never seen. Clarence makes it his mission to befriend the mysterious neighbor, only to find out it's someone he knows quite well.

added.title: Water Park
added.description: The trio heads to Squirty's Moist Mountain water park, and as Clarence learns the truth about his idol Squirty, Jeff and Sumo wait in line for the reopening of the parks tallest slide, The Curd Churner.

added.title: The Big Petey Pizza Problem
added.description: Jeff has everything in place for his birthday at Papa Petey's Pins and Pies but Gilben is also having his party there, stealing Jeff's thunder. Jeff gets even more upset when the kids suggest they merge their parities for a double birthday. Can Jeff learn to roll with the punches and share his special day?

added.title: The Break Up
added.description: A silly argument between Jeff and Sumo escalates until they vow never to speak to each other again. At first Clarence enjoys the separation, now he's always got someone to play with but eventually he becomes exhausted and must hatch a scheme to get the guys to be friends again.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: Home, Sweet Homesick
added.description: When the Girls go to Camp, Blossom has a hard time leaving her schoolwork at home.

added.title: Never Been Blissed
added.description: With a parasitic alien on the loose in their school, the Powerpuff Girls and Bliss have to find a way to stop it before the big dance.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: Goat!
added.description: Prohyas becomes obsessed with riding an uncooperative goat to get over a mountain.

added.title: Agent of Destruction
added.description: DeBizz helps the Warriors become more famous as their agent, but Vambre returns to adventuring while Prohyas gets caught up in the DeBizz fame trap.

added.title: Dunkadellic
added.description: After suffering trauma from being the dunk-ee in a dunking booth, Prohyas has trouble getting through the dunk based traps in Man Fish's lair.

added.title: Bureaucrophobia
added.description: Teri Gargantuan is in trouble and her spider kids hire the Warriors to save their mom from a mad mercenary spider hunter.

added.title: Hunting for Scavengers
added.description: When an impish weather gnome sends the Warriors and friends on a competitive quest, the drive to win threatens the group's fight against a conjured monster.

added.title: Unconventional Dolphinism
added.description: Since Prohyas is taking Dolphin Magisword to the Dolphin Convention, Vambre asks Witchy Simone to join her on a search for the Narwhal Magisword, angering a deadly Sealdebeast guard that lures dolphins away from the convention in the process.

added.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
added.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

added.title: Bad Heir Day
added.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

added.title: Orb
added.description: The dreams of Finn, Jake, and BMO fall under the influence of a mysterious orb.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Bun Bun
added.description: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

added.title: Horse and Ball
added.description: When disaster befalls James Baxter, it's up to Finn and Jake to help him pick up the pieces.

added.title: Jelly Beans Have Power
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's scientific mind must wrestle with her Elemental magic potential when she's faced with a Crystal Entity.

added.title: Football
added.description: Football and BMO strike a bargain that may prove too difficult for one of them to keep.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Thanks for the Crabapples, Guiseppe
added.description: Ice King and a band of misfit wizards go on a mystical road trip.

added.title: Princess Potluck
added.description: Ice King gets super jealous when he finds out that he wasn't invited to the Princess Potluck.

added.title: Red Starved
added.description: Finn, Jake and Marceline are trapped in an underground cavern with no red in sight. If Marceline doesn't feed, like ASAP, she will turn into a vampiric beast and suck out all of Jake's blood! So, Finn heads off to explore the cave and find something red to satiate her until they can be rescued. But time is running out!

added.title: Hot to the Touch
added.description: Finn goes on a quest to prove Flame Princess isn't really evil.

added.title: Thank You
added.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.

added.title: Paper Pete
added.description: The pages of the books in the Ooo library turn to Finn & Jake for help before the evil Moldari destroy them.

added.title: Mystery Train
added.description: Finn and Jake get wrapped up in a high speed whodunit!

added.title: Slumber Party Panic
added.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: Ben 10,000
added.description: Ben gets sucked into the future by a grown up Gwen. His mission is to help the now all powerful and adult Ben 10,000 seemingly defeat the future versions of Dr. Animo and Vilgax. However, the real reason Ben has been brought to the future is to teach his adult self some humility and the fact he's lost touch with Max and has forgotten what's really important, family.

added.title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Collateral Damage
added.description: Soundwave finally escapes the Shadow Zone to set up a Beacon Generator intended to summon Megatron! While the Bee Team engages the notorious Decepticon atop a skyscraper, Optimus Prime takes on Laserbeak in the skies over Crown City, and Sideswipe learns a lesson in considering the consequences of his actions.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: Under a Red Sun
added.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Hat Trick
added.description: When Felix Faust steals Zatanna's magical top hat, the Justice League must help retrieve it before the evil wizard can use it to create a magic portal, releasing the demon Ghast.

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: Supernatural Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Stargirl has to enlist Constantine's help when Klarion the Witch Boy takes the place of the boy she's supposed to be babysitting.

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: An American Benwolf in London
added.description: Ben and Rook are called to London England to investigate the Forever Knights' latest activities.

added.title: Wasteland
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa neglects his garbage duties, he embarks on a quest to save his friends from the overflowing pile of trash.

added.title: Fries Night
added.description: Benson wants some french fries to overcome his depression.

added.title: Chili Cook-Off
added.description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: The Thanksgiving Special
added.description: The park guys need to get Thanksgiving dinner for their families to save Thanksgiving.

added.title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito
added.description: Rigby wants to accomplish at least one thing he said he would accomplish before his High School reunion.

added.title: Party Re-Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to save Benson from an evil party company.

added.title: Steak Me Amadeus
added.description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Superman's Pal, Sid Sharp
added.description: When obnoxious reporter Sid Sharp decides that Clark Kent is getting all his stories because of his connection to Superman, Sid decides to become his own superhero to out scoop him.

added.title: Hermano-lipsis
added.description: Cuando los chicos están heridos, Raven y Starfire deben convertirse en "hermanos" para detener el Hermano-lipsis.

added.title: Camarones y Costillas
added.description: Los Titanes intentan recordar cómo ser superhéroes para detener a Cerebro.

added.title: Agua de Ensalada Caliente
added.description: Robin debe salvar a los Estados Unidos de una nueva invasión británica cuando beber té vuelve ingleses a los demás Titanes.

added.title: Inaccion de Gracias
added.description: Llegó el Día de Acción de Gracias y los Titanes, hartos de las tradiciones normales, inventan una propia.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 1
added.description: Cuando su mundo comienza a desaparecer, los Titanes deben confrontar a sus creadores.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 2
added.description: Los Titanes descubren lo difícil que es producir dibujos animados cuando hacen uno sobre Michael y Aaron.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Internet Troll
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus venture into cyberspace to defeat an Internet troll.

added.title: Tiger and Mouse
added.description: An unlikely friendship between Giant Realistic Flying Tiger and a mouse threatens to destroy everything inside the RV.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Diary
added.description: When his diary winds up in the hands of Mr. Gus, Pizza Steve goes to great lengths to get it back before Mr. Gus can read all of his deepest, darkest secrets.

added.title: Big Trouble for Tiny Miracle
added.description: Tiny Miracle allows the gang to take advantage of his generosity at the expense of his own health.

added.title: King of the Hill Part 1
added.description: Overconfidence leaves the Bee Team unprepared when they face a Stunticon that can fire guided missiles…on the desert ground above a nuclear waste disposal site!

added.title: Defrosted
added.description: Grimlock begs to learn new fighting methods from reluctant "teacher" Drift and puts them into action when The Autobots travel to the Antarctic to battle the Decepticon Prong - unfrozen from a melting glacier. Grim must put Drift's lessons to use in order to defeat the Decepticon and save the research team stuck there.

added.title: Sphere of Influence
added.description: The Bee Team discovers a mysterious artifact that has a strange effect on Cybertronian minds, turning the bots against one another! Can the Bee Team get it together in time to keep obsessed treasure-­hunter Springload from accidentally destroying Crown City?

added.title: The Great Divide
added.description: After once again accidentally combining into the Ultra Bee Team Combiner, the Autobots find Sideswipe has split into two individuals -­ each being one extreme of his personality. Now, the two Sideswipes must overcome their differences and learn to work together as the Bee Team pursues Stunticon Drag Strip, who stole a dangerous Cybertronian device - the Gravitic Adjuster.

added.title: Out of the Shadows
added.description: The Bee Team learns about Drift's past when his former mentor Shadow Raker comes to Earth to recover something Drift has taken from him‑ Slipstream and Jetstorm!

added.title: Guilty as Charged
added.description: Strongarm worries that her Academy classmate Chicane may still harbor a grudge, but when a powerful foe comes after her old friend, Strongarm and the Bee Team put their sparks on the line to protect her.

added.title: The Fastest Bot Alive!
added.description: Grimlock acquires uncontrollable superspeed, which proves to be a problem when the Autobots have to deal with a revenge‑minded Simacore and his army of Mini‑Con clones.

added.title: Combine and Conquer
added.description: Feeling the Autobots need to step up their game, Bee insists they follow his orders to the letter.
